<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOWARD SOUNDS OFF ON DROPS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVINE, Calif. _ USC wide receiver R. Jay Soward criticized
himself Wednesday over his inconsistent performance in training
camp, which has been marked by a flurry of dropped passes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't done anything. I'm not even good. I feel like I'm
sorry right now,'' Soward said.
</P>
<P>
   Soward has dropped balls with regularity and finally lost his
patience.
</P>
<P>
   ``Maybe we should let the freshmen start a couple practices,''
Soward said. ``I'm not playing good.''
</P>
<P>
   Soward said his problems stem from thinking about making big
plays in practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm trying to do too much. I'm thinking about scoring before
catching the ball,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   During the team's first practice in pads, Soward had several
outbursts _ some directed at the defense. On one play, defensive
back Kris Richard grabbed Soward by the face mask and tossed him to
the ground.
</P>
<P>
   ``They were grabbing my face mask. Throwing me down. Maybe it's
the way they're taught defense,'' Soward said. ``I'm not going to
cry about it. I can't call (a penalty).''
</P>
<P>
   __ Freshman recap: So which of the freshmen will not redshirt?
</P>
<P>
   Wide receivers Marcell Allmond, Kareem Kelly and Steve
Stevenson, cornerback Darrell Rideaux and defensive tackle Bernard
Riley will all play this season. Whether offensive lineman Lenny
Vandermade or linebacker Aaron Graham redshirt is not decided.
</P>
<P>
   But one player who is opening eyes is linebacker Omar Nazel. He
might be playing himself out of a redshirt year, depending on USC's
depth at weakside linebacker.
</P>
<P>
   __ Steele update: Another day passed without any change on
linebacker Markus Steele's status. He's waiting for his JC
transcripts to be forwarded to USC.
</P>
<P>
   __ Position change: Redshirt freshman Anthony Daye has been
switched from linebacker to defensive end.
</P>
<P>
   __ Guards set: Hackett said Donta Kendrick is firmly entrenched
as the starter at left guard. There's a battle taking place at
right guard, where senior Jason Grain and freshman Zach Wilson are
the candidates.
</P>
<P>
   __ Making an impact: One player who has been a pleasant surprise
is sophomore Lonnie Ford, who is splitting time with Kori Dickerson
at defensive end. Ford was a tight end his first two seasons, until
requesting a position change last spring.
</P>
<P>
   ``Now, I'm in a situation where I can go out and play. I can
surprise a lot of people this season,'' Ford said. ``There was no
use for me to be on offense. I wasn't really making any plays.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury report: Linebacker Jason Steen suffered a neck injury
and underwent X-rays Tuesday afternoon. USC coach Paul Hackett did
not think the injury was serious. . . . Defensive tackle Aaron
Williams suffered a sprained ankle and might be out two days. . . .
Offensive tackle Brent McCaffrey (punctured foot) returned to
practice and appeared fine. . . . Offensive tackle Matt Welch
missed practice with a sore shoulder.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
