<HEADLINE>
FIRST AMERICAN AGREES TO BUY OLATHE TITLE COMPANY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ERIC PALMER  
 c. 1997 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   First American Title Insurance Co., the largest title insurer in
the country, has agreed to acquire Security Land Title Co. of
Olathe, Kan.
</P>
<P>
   The proposed acquisition comes four months after First American
extended its market share in the area by purchasing the three
Guarantee Title operations in Johnson, Wyandotte and Leavenworth
counties.
</P>
<P>
   Security Land Title has 11 offices and about 210 employees, all
of whom will be retained, according to Jack Kerwin, Security Land
Title's president.
</P>
<P>
   Security Land Title, which was founded in 1974, is owned by
Kerwin, Ed Gomez, Terry Anderson and Bill Perry. Gomez is executive
vice president, Anderson is senior vice president, and Perry is
executive vice president and general counsel.
</P>
<P>
   The company will continue to operate as Security Land Title and
the four principals will remain in their management positions,
Kerwin said.
</P>
<P>
   The deal is expected to be completed by Oct. 1, after reviews by
the U.S. Commerce Department and the Justice Department, Kerwin
said. He declined to give details of the deal, except to say it was
a stock transaction. Security had revenue of about $15 million last
year, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The owners of Security had decided in the spring to solicit bids
for the company, Kerwin said, and received preliminary offers from
two other national firms. He said Security chose First American's
bid because of what it offered employees and because of its
resources to acquire technology.
</P>
<P>
   First American Title Insurance Co. is a subsidiary of First
American Financial of Santa Ana, Calif. The publicly traded parent
company has nearly 20,000 employees in more than 600 branch offices
in the United States and abroad and says it is the nation's leading
provider of business information. In addition to title insurance
and mortgage origination and servicing, it sells home warranties,
and performs credit reporting and other services.
</P>
<P>
   First American had net income of about $200 million last year on
revenue of $2.8 billion.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
