   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-LAUNDER (Undated) _ Billions of dollars have been
channeled through the Bank of New York in the last year in what is
believed to be a major money laundering operation by Russian
organized crime, law enforcement officials say. By Raymond Bonner
with Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
<P>
   TURKEY-SCENE (Izmet, Turkey) _ People here spent their day
digging, sifting, grieving and increasingly despairing that those
who have not escaped from the rubble by now are probably dead. They
watched as bulldozers and front-end loaders tried to unearth
bedrooms, which is where most people were when the earthquake
struck. Then in the swirl of dust and smoke and sweltering heat,
residents picked through the rubble with hammers and chisels and
bare hands. As delicately as archaeologists, they teased out shreds
of clothing, old photos, scraps of furniture and, inevitably, the
bodies. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NY-PAROLE (New York) _ Memos unearthed by the U.S. attorney's
office in its investigation into Gov. George Pataki's fund raising
provide a rare view of the close ties between Pataki administration
officials and aides at the governor's political arm. By Clifford J.
Levy and Laurie Flynn.
</P>
<P>
   LUTHERAN-EPISCOPAL (Denver) _ As leaders of the nation's largest
Lutheran denomination gather to debate one of the most important
ecumenical proposals in decades, controversy over that proposal has
produced an unusually energetic display of the push and pull of
politics within a church. What's at stake is a sweeping agreement
for close cooperation between the Evangelical Lutheran Church in
America and the Episcopal Church, a proposal that many here liken
to a marriage. By Gustav Niebuhr.
</P>
<P>
   JUDGES-DEATH-PENALTY (Atlanta) _ In a highly unusual meeting
that has angered death penalty opponents, southern federal judges
from the 11th circuit court of appeals are having a conference at a
super luxury resort on how to expedite capital punishment,
demonstrating the determined attempt to keep the death penalty
alive in the South. By David Firestone.
</P>
