   &UR; BUSINESS DAY _ (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DAYTRADING-MARKETPLACE _ Harvey Houtkin is chief executive of
All-Tech Investment Group, one of the nation's largest day-trading
firms. And he says that his company, which provides computerized
stock market access to individuals, enables anyone with a
willingness to learn _ and $25,000 _ to open an account, to make a
living trading stocks. But since a day trader killed nine people in
Atlanta last month _ five of them at an All-Tech office _ Houtkin's
operation has come under intense regulatory scrutiny. By Gretchen
Morgenson.
</P>
