</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ARTS (Tokyo) _ Famous art is leaving Japan, and only a
handful of bankers and art dealers know for sure where it is going.
The paintings, including large numbers of van Goghs, Modiglianis,
Renoirs and Picassos that vanished into Japan more than a decade
ago, are being resold abroad as a result of the country's economic
collapse. ``There's a loss of face associated with this art,'' said
Chieko Hasegawa, owner of the Nichido Gallery in Ginza. ``The sale
of these paintings sends two messages: that you have financial
difficulties and that you paid too much for them from the start.''
By Stephanie Strom.
