California lag far behind those of other ethnic groups, and a
corresponding lack of education is the main culprit, according to a
report released to state legislators. With a median income of
$14,560 a year, Latinos make about $8,000 less than the next-lowest
group, African Americans, according to the report. By EMILY GURNON.
