on the Hispanic Decade. (Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor of
the Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Should pols' drug use be
forgiven? Is it our business? Can George W. Bush refuse to discuss
drug use? If Bush's answer was no, we'd probably have heard it long
ago. Oddly, Bush gets some cover from Clinton's tryst with Monica
Lewinsky. Americans got so sick of having the details rubbed in
their face that a majority may agree the question is irrelevant.
But can he turn what some politicians and reporters think is big
stuff into a nonissue? Over the next 15 months, we'll find out.
(McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
