<P>
   TRAVEL-LLAMA _ PISGAH NATIONAL FOREST, N.C. _ B.B. the llama is
famished. Or so it seems. The 13-year-old, 400-pound pack animal
that trails me through a deliriously lush stretch of maintain
wilderness in the Pisgah National Forest is snarfing every
chlorophyll-producing thing in sight _ pine needles, hemlock
leaves, clumps of pungent sassafras, you name it. It's part of the
charm of English Mountain Llama Treks, unusual guided excursions
begun four years ago. Drawing from a stable of 30 llamas, the
owners add an element of animal magnetism to day hikes through
Pisgah and overnight hikes through the nearby Nantahala National
Forest. (Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH COLOR PHOTOS.
