granola-eating ring to it. A place so pastoral and picture-perfect
rustic that L.L. Bean has photographed two catalogs of country
couture here. Yet, first-timers never know exactly what to expect
from this back-to-nature getaway in the Blue Ridge
Mountians.(Thrasher, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
