<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ BUDAPEST _ Hungary's geography is its
history, both past and future. ``Hungary is located at the very
center of the conflict between East and West,'' said Professor
Ferenc Gazdag, 52, director of the Institute for Strategic and
Defense Studies. The Kosovo war was no exception. (Murray, Cox News
Service) MOVED WEDNESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN _ Remembering the good old days. (Ernest
Murray is managing editor of The Lufkin Daily News) EMBARGOED for
Sunday. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ HOPKINTON, N.H. _ It is 45 degrees at 5:30 a.m.
on the 10th of August as I begin my walk-jog down Farrington Corner
Road. I am wearing a sweatshirt and shorts, the sweatshirt
purchased in the old ship-building town of Portsmouth the day
before, when I realized my East Texas-thinned blood was actually
cold while walking around. A novel feeling: cold in August. I'm
enjoying this time at my grandmother's house in New Hampshire.
(Gary Borders is editor and publisher of the Nacogdoches Daily
Sentinel.) EMBARGOED for Sunday. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Contrary to recent stories in
magazines, me and my middle-age Latino counterparts won't miss out
on the Hispanic Decade. (Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor of
the Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Should pols' drug use be
forgiven? Is it our business? Can George W. Bush refuse to discuss
drug use? If Bush's answer was no, we'd probably have heard it long
ago. Oddly, Bush gets some cover from Clinton's tryst with Monica
Lewinsky. Americans got so sick of having the details rubbed in
their face that a majority may agree the question is irrelevant.
But can he turn what some politicians and reporters think is big
stuff into a nonissue? Over the next 15 months, we'll find out.
(McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ This column will not move today.
(John Young is opinion page editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald)
</P>
