</P>
<P>
   AUTOS-COLUMN (Undated) _ It was what may have been the largest
gathering of steam cars, and as they traveled among heavy tourist
traffic they were centers of attention. By Royal Ford.
</P>
<P>
   AUTOS-REVIEW (Undated) _ The Viggen is the best Saab yet. It's
got power, it's got performance, it's wonderfully comfortable, and
in trained hands it can be fun. By Royal Ford.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Hedge fund manager Jon Jacobson,
who once made investment killings for the Harvard University
endowment, is a leading figure behind a hostile takeover battle for
Reynolds Metals. By Steven Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;   &UR; (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS-BLEDSOE (Smithfield, R.I.) _ The strengths of this
Patriots team are far and away its receivers, its tight end and its
quarterback. And Drew Bledsoe, now at his prime, is the key to it
all. By Michael Madden. 1000 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   HKN-HOLLEY-COLUMN (Boston) -- There's just no accounting for the
Bruins' delay on goalie Byron Dafoe. By Michael Holley.
</P>
