</P>
<P>
   TURKEY-GOLCUK (Golcuk, Turkey) _ The story from a town where
hundreds or even thousands may still be trapped beneath the rubble,
including sailors at a collapsed naval base. Residents here are
angry that the rescue efforts seem to be more focused on
servicemen. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   And
</P>
<P>
   TURKEY-BUILDINGS (Istanbul) _ Story on the buildings whose
shoddy construction was revealed by the earthquake; talking to
engineers, aid workers etc. By Celestine Bohlen.
