<HEADLINE>
`YELLOW SUBMARINE' RESURFACES 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By ROBERT SELTZER 
c. 1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
``Once upon a time _ or maybe twice _ there was an unearthly
paradise called Pepperland.'' 
_ From the movie ``Yellow Submarine'' 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ It was mayhem with a melody _ the chaotic but
lyrical ``Yellow Submarine.''
</P>
<P>
   And it is back.
</P>
<P>
   More than 30 years after it charmed the world, the animated
movie is returning, its colors so rich they seem to drip down the
screen.
</P>
<P>
   Available for the first time in 11 years, MGM Home Entertainment
is rereleasing ``Yellow Submarine'' on videocassette and DVD Sept.
14, each version digitally renovated, with the soundtrack remixed
in Dolby Surround Sound.
</P>
<P>
   The film boasts footage that was not seen in the original movie,
including a scene featuring ``Hey Bulldog,'' the roughest song on
the soundtrack.
</P>
<P>
   Like the Yellow Submarine itself, one of the most famous
vehicles in rock 'n' roll history, the movie takes you back in time
_ to a decade when the Beatles captivated the world with their
humor and whimsy.
</P>
<P>
   As the cartoon version of John Lennon says, ``It's all in the
mind.''
</P>
<P>
   Unlike the music, or the images, the plot is simple: The
adventure is set in a psychedelic world called Pepperland, where
the Beatles have vowed to rescue the citizens from the Blue
Meanies, who have declared war on all that is good.
</P>
<P>
   The Beatles may not be warriors, but they wield a weapon, their
music, which reduces the Blue Meanies to whimpering nasties.
</P>
<P>
   Ah, yes, the music, raucous one minute, ethereal the next _ the
soundtrack to a dream.
</P>
<P>
   The movie features such classics as ``Eleanor Rigby,'' ``Nowhere
Man,'' ``All You Need Is Love'' and ``Lucy in the Sky With
Diamonds.''
</P>
<P>
   As they cavort their way through this adventure, the Beatles
meet giant apes, flying fists and a pair of disembodied feet with
floppy socks that do not match.
</P>
<P>
   All in all, it is a magical mystery tour. ... No, wait a minute
_ different album, different movie.
</P>
<P>
   The ``Yellow Submarine'' DVD, available in the original
wide-screen format, features the theatrical trailer and a
behind-the-scenes short, ``The Mod Odyssey.'' The videocassette is
$19.98, while the DVD sells for $29.98.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXXXXX END OF STORY
</P>
</TEXT>
