<HEADLINE>
EDITORS:    
</HEADLINE>
  
 Thursday, Aug. 19, 1999
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service will file this additional story for
Friday in the ``w'' category:
</P>
<P>
   CLARK-READINESS (Washington) _ In a sign of the Pentagon's
widening campaign to regain use of an island bombing range in
Puerto Rico, Gen. Wesley Clark, the NATO commander in Europe,
expresses concern that American forces ``may not be fully combat
ready'' without resumption of live-fire training on Vieques. Clark
says combat-style training on Vieques is essential for American
forces bound for Europe. By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   PLASTICIZERS (Washington) _ A federal panel will offer its
advice on the safety of plasticizers, an ingredient used in many
plastics. This is the latest step in a running battle between the
plastics industry and environmental groups over the safety of the
material. By DAVID IVANOVICH.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
</TEXT>
