<P>
   The New York Times Syndicate offers religion columns by Mike
McManus and Diana Butler Bass. Here are this week's columns:
</P>
<P>
   DIVERSE SOCIETY MUST UNDERSTAND AND ACCEPT ITS RELIGIOUS
SYMBOLS, by Diana Butler Bass
</P>
<P>
   We live in a culture full of conflicting religious symbols. When
they collide, we tend to respond as the Mississippi authorities did
to Ryan Green and his Star of David. Hide them. Tuck them away. Do
not display your beliefs in public. We strip the public square of
crosses, crescents, and stars and threaten legal action if another
faith offends us. That strategy seems, however, to have failed.
Radically privatizing faith has contributed to greater
misunderstanding and prejudice.
</P>
<P>
   (Slugged BC-STAR-OF-DAVID-NYTSF)
</P>
