<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-19 18:13 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3209 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-MOVIES-TINGLE20-COX     08-19 0396
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIES-TINGLE20-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Teaching' needs better lesson plan has flawed lesson plans
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   As high school movies go, ``Teaching Mrs. Tingle'' barely makes
a passing grade. It never gets a firm grip on what it is. High
school horror flick? Smart-aleck teen hostage tale? Nasty-nice
Disney movie with devilish undertones?
</P>
<P>
   Gifted actress Helen Mirren stars as high school history teacher
Mrs. Tingle. She's a born-to-be-bad one _ the kind of testy,
high-minded, hard-grading instructor who openly puts down her
students. Her greatest joy is making them feel worthless.
</P>
<P>
   Across the classroom sits Leigh Ann (Katie Holmes), the
hard-working student needing one more A to make class valedictorian
and land a much-needed college scholarship. And the charmer Luke
(Barry Watson), whom she secretly loves. And her gal pal Jo Lynn
(Marisa Coughlan), who has her sights set on being a mega movie
star.
</P>
<P>
   In a series of misunderstandings and mishaps, these kids
ultimately take Mrs. Tingle hostage in her own home _ a fairly posh
one for a teacher _ tying her to her bed and then spending several
days figuring out how they're going to get out of the mess they've
just created. Otherwise, how is poor Leigh Ann going to get to
college?
</P>
<P>
   As if anybody will care.
</P>
<P>
   Writer-director Kevin Williamson (aka Mr. ``Scream'') has made,
in effect, an end-of-the-century remake of that silly, fluffy 1980
Lily Tomlin-Jane Fonda-Dolly Parton comedy ``Nine to Five.'' Only
not nearly as witty and never as funny.
</P>
<P>
   Mirren gallantly makes a go of it. She's testy, manipulative,
conniving and, by midway into the movie, quite convincing.
</P>
<P>
   Holmes and Watson seem to be here because they're young WB stars
_ she of ``Dawson's Creek'' and he of ``7th Heaven.'' Their main
contribution is a fairly lusty roll in Mrs. Tingle's living room.
</P>
<P>
   Sadly, it's the moment at which most kids in the audience will
sit up and take notes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Teaching
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Tingle''
</P>
<P>
   Grade: C-
</P>
<P>
   Starring Helen Mirren, Katie Holmes, Barry Watson and Marisa
Coughlan. Written and directed by Kevin Williamson. Rated PG-13 for
thematic content, violence, sexuality, language and teenage
drinking. 1 hour, 35 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   The verdict: Go to the back of the class.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
