Chris Chandler. Graziani will play most of Saturday's game against
Baltimore. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-ALABAMA _ The Road to College Football travels to Alabama,
where the sex scandal surrouding coach Mike DuBose - and not the
team - is the talk of the state. Many vocal fans are against
DuBose. Others have publicly harassed the woman with whom he had an
affair and who later filed a lawsuit against him. The school
considered firing him before it shortened his contract and reduced
his compensation. Athletic Director Bob Bockrath says information
not available to the public kept him from firing DuBose. The school
trustees asked the university president to tell them what's going
on. A bad start could mean the end of DuBose's tenure. (Barnhart,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GTECHLINE _ ATLANTA _ It is huge, averaging just under 300
pounds per player, and experienced, with nine total letters earned.
Led by All-America candidate Jon Carman at one tackle and All-ACC
candidate Chris Brown at the other, Georgia Tech's offensive line
hold the Jackets' season _ and quarterback Joe Hamilton's Heisman
hopes -- in its massive hands. (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
