lead in the Winston Cup points standings? The 300-point advantage
is so enormous that the Ford No. 88 driver could finish last and
next-to-last in the next two races, including Sunday's Pepsi 400,
and still be No. 1 in the standings. (Carvell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
