candidate Chris Brown at the other, Georgia Tech's offensive line
hold the Jackets' season _ and quarterback Joe Hamilton's Heisman
hopes -- in its massive hands. (Clemons, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR
</P>
<P>
   CAR-JARRETT _ With 13 races remaining, Dale Jarrett has one of
the biggest points leads in NASCAR history (300), so big in fact,
that it would be almost impossible to lose the Winston Cup title.
Thought for the rest of the season: Show up, and be on time.
(Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 17.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-NASCAR-ITEMS _ NASCAR odds and ends package. (Carvell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-NASCAR-NOTES _ NASCAR notebook. (Carvell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET NASCAR PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Here is the budget for this week's CoxNet NASCAR page. The
layout is available.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET NASCAR 0820: BIG LEAD _ How outrageous is Dale Jarrett's
lead in the Winston Cup points standings? The 300-point advantage
is so enormous that the Ford No. 88 driver could finish last and
next-to-last in the next two races, including Sunday's Pepsi 400,
and still be No. 1 in the standings. (Carvell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
