<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ALBUM-OF-THE-WEEK-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ALBUM OF THE WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 By ANN POWERS    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHRISTINA AGUILERA: ``Christina Aguilera'' (RCA/BMG). Build a
better nymphet: it's a lucrative proposition, with female
teen-age-oriented artists still relatively rare, and the appeal of
such imaginary girlfriends proved by the success of Britney Spears.
The challenge also has a moral dimension, since it means
acknowledging that girls are expressing their sexuality younger
than ever.
</P>
<P>
   One of the summer's catchiest singles captures the moment's
anxieties about teen-age sex. ``Genie in a Bottle,'' sung by the
blue-eyed former Mouseketeer Christina Aguilera, is a skittish
dance hit propelled by indecision.
</P>
<P>
   ``My body's sayin' let's go,'' the 18-year-old singer whispers,
``but my heart is saying no.'' The chorus then spirals upward,
riding bubbly dance beats, as Ms. Aguilera declares herself the
kind of genie who appears only when rubbed ``the right way.''
</P>
<P>
   This double-entendre, shocking to some, nonetheless expresses a
distinctly female sexual need and imagines a self-aware Ms.
Aguilera in charge of it. It has topped the Billboard Hot 100 chart
for weeks.
</P>
<P>
   This singer's full-length debut, out this Tuesday, is engineered
to keep her there. The pop empress Diane Warren wrote two ballads:
a Whitney Houston-style rave-up, ``I Turn to You,'' and the bouncy
``Somebody's Somebody,'' in which Ms. Aguilera seems to replicate
herself as an En Vogue-like girl group. ``Love Will Find a Way''
gains spice from a reliable Jackson Five-style bass line. The
flamboyant Star Search-style ballad ``Reflection'' was on the
``Mulan'' soundtrack.
</P>
<P>
   Beyond its sleek design, this album hints at a real singer's
emergence. She has striking vocal power and range, if not a clue
about expressing individuality. Once she has fulfilled the
requirements of a teen-age pinup, she may enlist her bold talent to
make music as personally nuanced as ``Genie in a Bottle'' is
serendipitous.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
