   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BIRTH-CERTIFICATES (Brownsville, Texas) _ The INS has identified
2,000 Mexican citizens whose children have phony U.S. birth
certificates and they are telling them to come forward or risk
arrest on fraud charges. The names are the result of the arrests a
few years ago of 13 midwives charged with selling thousands of the
phony documents to parents who wanted their children to be able to
claim U.S. citizenship and attend Texas schools. By JAMES
PINKERTON. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   MENTAL-TEXAS (Austin, Texas) _ The state's mental health agency,
suffering from a $30 million budget shortfall, has pledged not to
cut any services for at least three months and says it will fully
fund new drug treatments. By POLLY ROSS HUGHES. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ It is difficult to respect a
presidential candidate who lacks the courage to say whether he or
she believes in biological evolution. George W. Bush, Elizabeth
Dole and Steve Forbes ducked the question, saying they would leave
it to the states rather than the scientific community to decide
whether Charles Darwin was a jerk. Such ignorant mush could be
expected of Forbes, who is pandering to the religious right, but
Dole promised us she would give us straight talk. By MARIANNE
MEANS. (Already filed.)
