<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, Aug. 20. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
GROWCOST (Phoenix) - We hear about the economic benefits of growth
_ a bigger tax base, new jobs, new businesses _ but what are the
costs of growth to a city or county or school district? Let's look
at the cost based on a single family home in a new neighborhood.
What demands do they make of the city and local schools? A new
family in a new subdivison means more people on the road, which
means more roads are needed, as are more police, firefighters,
garbage trucks, water, sewer lines, schools, stores _ it's a domino
effect. On the flip side, most planners say single family housing
does not pay for itself, which means money for all the needed
services has to come from somewhere else. How does it all fit
together? By SHAUN MCKINNON. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
COFFEE (Phoenix) - It may be the most coveted herb in the world.
And the most controversial. The truth is that coffee is a complex
liquid, and how it affects our health is still being looked into.
However, based on the most recent round of studies, it appears that
drinking moderate amounts of coffee _ two to three cups a day _
does little harm and may actually provide health benefits. By
THOMAS ROPP. Story moved in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NOTARO-COLUMN (Phoenix) - I've heard urban legends in which people
buy a computer, take it out of the box, plug it in and it actually
works. Things like that just do not happen.
</P>
<P>
   Especially not to me. That's not the way things work in my
world. By LAURI NOTARO. Story moved in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
GOODY-TV (Undated) _ Introducing Dorothy Dandridge is a
worthy-but-flawed HBO original movie that does just that _
introduces us to the first black woman ever nominated for a Best
Actress Oscar. It would have been far more satisfying to get to
know her better. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story will move in the ``E''
category. &QL; 
