program. This is the first major retailer to join the program and
it could lead to an end for paper-based scrip programs. By Tom
Stein
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BESTBUY &LR;  _ Today, Best Buy continues its Bay Area blitz by
opening five stores, bringing the total number launched locally to
this year seven. The stores, which cover a broad market from Marin
to Milpitas to Dublin, will change the landscape in home
electronics retailing, posing a particular threat to homegrown Good
Guys. By Carol Emert
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUANTUM &LR;  _ Hard-hit by fierce competition and shifting markets,
Milpitas' Quantum Corp. plans to lay off up to 800 employees and
restructure its business to focus on drives for the sub-$700 PCs.
By Henry Norr
</P>
