<SLUG> BC-RAC-QUIET-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
REAL QUIET JOINS CLASSIC DROPOUTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ A leg fracture has made Real Quiet the latest
Horse of the Year contender to drop out of the Aug. 29 Pacific
Classic at Del Mar.
</P>
<P>
   The injury, a fracture in the splint bone behind the 4-year-old
colt's right shin, was discovered in X-rays after swelling appeared
following a workout Sunday morning at Santa Anita.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not a very severe injury, certainly not
life-threatening,'' Eoin Harty, an assistant to trainer Bob
Baffert, said Thursday from Del Mar. ``But it'll put him out for at
least 90 days. He won't race again this year.''
</P>
<P>
   Harty described the injury as ``no worse than breaking a
finger.'' Yet the timing prompted speculation owner Mike Pegram
will retire the 1998 Kentucky Derby and Preakness winner in time
for the 2000 breeding season.
</P>
<P>
   Real Quiet, whose biggest local victories came in the '97
Hollywood Futurity and the June 27 Hollywood Gold Cup, has won 6 of
20 starts and more than $3.2 million. He missed a $5 million Triple
Crown bonus when Victory Gallop beat him by a nose in the '98
Belmont Stakes.
</P>
<P>
   Coincidentally, news of his injury came a week after Victory
Gallop was retired with a suspensory-ligament tear.
</P>
<P>
   Without Victory Gallop, Real Quiet and NTRA Champions on Fox
series points leader Behrens, the Pacific Classic figures to have a
small, all-Californian field. Mazel Trick looks like a heavy
favorite in the 1\-mile race against Bobby Frankel barnmate Barter
Town, Baffert-trained General Challenge and River Keen, and Malek.
</P>
<P>
   Behrens is passing up a shot at a $330,000 series bonus _ and
the $600,000 winner's share of the $1 million Pacific Classic purse
_ because trainer Jim Bond wants to keep him in the East before the
$4 million Breeders' Cup Classic at Gulfstream Park in Florida.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
