u f BC-NYTIMES-EXEC-NYT &LR;      08-19 0147
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NYTIMES-EXEC-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EXECUTIVE AT TIMES GETS EXPANDED ROLE 
</HEADLINE>
  (pr) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Marc Z. Kramer, the vice president for labor
relations at The New York Times, has received additional
responsibility for production, the newspaper's president, Janet L.
Robinson, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Kramer, who joined The Times in May 1998 after serving as vice
president and general counsel at The Daily News, is assuming the
production duties from David A. Thurm, who was recently appointed
chief operating officer of Times Company Digital, the Internet unit
of the paper's parent company.
</P>
<P>
   Before his work at The Daily News, Kramer, 44, was an associate
specializing in labor law at Proskauer Rose Goetz &AMP; Mendelsohn.
Between 1985 and 1990, he was deputy general counsel and general
counsel at the Mayor's Office of Labor Relations in New York City.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
