The Evangelical Lutheran Church of America on Thursday voted to
approve ``full communion'' with the Episcopalian Church,
representing a unity pact the two churches have been working toward
for 30 years. The Rev David Perry, who has led the Episcopal
Church's movement for ``full communion'' with the Evangelical
Lutheran Church, breaks house rules by calling friends and church
officials with news Thursday's vote. (Kevin Moloney/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) DENVER -- Aug. 19, 1999 -- LUTHERAN-EPISCOPAL, 08-19 --
Pastor Molly Doreza of the South-Central Wisconsin Synod of the
Evangelical Lutheran Church in America gets a congratulatory hug
from PastorJoyce Heintz follwing Thursday's vote in favor of an
agreement with the Epsicopal Church. The sweeping agreement for
close cooperation between the Evangelical Lutheran Church in
America and the Episcopal Church, binds the two denominations in a
pact that recognizes each other's sacraments, share clergy members
where needed and engage in joint missionary and social service
work. (Kevin Moloney/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
