-- Tim Ream makes his way to a platform a hundred and twenty feet
above the forest floor where he will spend the night. Ream is part
of a loosely-knit environmental group opposed to a proposed trade
of public land, much of it in the Gifford Pinchot National Forest
in southwest Washington state, to the Plum Creek Timber Co. (Dan
DeLong/Seattle Post-Intelligencer Photo)
</P>
