<P>
   (NYT21) IRAPUATO, Mexico -- Aug. 19, 1999 --
MEXICO-BRACEROS-COX, 08-19 -- Consuelo Delgado, 70, and her
granddaughter during a protest claiming back wages. The protesters,
known as ``Braceros,'' are a handful of the 4.5 million Mexican
guest workers who were recruited to work on American farms for 22
years, beginning during World War II. Decades later, they have
formed a movement and are claiming the Mexican government owes them
as much as $3 billion, money that was deducted from their paychecks
and deposited into Mexican bank accounts that have mysteriously
disappeared.(Sergio Dorantes/Cox News Service)
</P>
