presidential speechwriter, outside the West Wing of the White
House. Earlier this month, Clinton named the 49-year-old Edmonds to
replace his veteran chief speech writer, Michael Waldman, who
decided to leave the administration. Since 1997, Edmonds has been
associate commissioner for public affairs at the Social Security
Administration, but earlier he worked in the White House Office of
Speech Writing, including a stint as deputy director. (Rick
McKay/Cox News Service) LITE
</P>
