<SLUG> BC-MA-BLUTE-GIDGET-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WOMAN WHO BARED BREASTS A STUNT DOUBLE, ACTRESS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL CROWLEY AND FRANK PHILLIPS AND FRANK PHILLIPS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON -- The mystery woman who bared her breasts at a news
photographer at the end of a controversial harbor cruise this week
had only days earlier attended a private fund-raiser for Governor
Paul Cellucci, sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The woman was identified as Gidget Churchill, a stunt double and
actress who has appeared on the television shows ``Melrose Place''
and ``Beverly Hills 90210,'' and the movies ``Celtic Pride,'' and
``Clueless.''
</P>
<P>
   Churchill's on-line resume says she has also doubled for such
actresses as Jennifer Aniston and Kathy Ireland, and appeared in
the racy Showtime series ``Red Shoe Diaries.''
</P>
<P>
   Churchill's identity became known Thursday, as pictures of her
baring her chest appeared repeatedly on television, serving as a
tawdry defining image for the cruise-boat scandal that claimed the
job of Massport executive director Peter Blute Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Sources said Churchill was aboard the 70-foot cabin cruiser
Nautica Tuesday afternoon as a guest of Massport consultant David
McCool, a former advance man for the governor. Neither McCool nor
Churchill returned calls Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Photographs of the cruise first appeared in the Wednesday Boston
Herald.
</P>
<P>
   Churchill also attended a Cellucci fund-raiser last week
arranged by Massport board member and local Teamster leader George
Cashman and by Lorna McCool, David McCool's sister.
</P>
<P>
   Both Blute and GOP lobbyist Alexander ``Sandy'' Tennant, who
joined Blute on the cruise that has rocked the Cellucci
administration, said they did not know Churchill.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have no idea who she is,'' Blute said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Churchill's resume was posted at the Web site of Gravity Works,
a California-based company that specializes in amusement park
rides, extreme sports equipment, and movie and television stunts.
</P>
<P>
   The resume lists stunts she has performed for 11 movies and
television shows. The stunts include ``Bike Fall, Near Miss,'' for
the television show ``Double Rush,'' ``High Fall'' for ``The Brady
Bunch Movie,'' and ``Non-Descript Stunts'' for ``Clueless'' and
``Beverly Hills 90210.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Special Skills'' featured on the resume include SCUBA diving,
jetskiing, motorcycling, and rapelling.
</P>
<P>
   Churchill has also been identified as a longtime supporter of
the Make a Wish Foundation, which raises money to grant wishes to
children with severe illnesses.
</P>
<P>
   Churchill's resume listed no date of birth, but sources said she
is in her mid-30s.
</P>
<P>
   As the political world buzzed about the cruise-boat debacle,
insiders pondered why a woman would expose herself to a
photographer in broad daylight and in the company of a top state
official. To some, a stunt artist for hire like Churchill fit
neatly into conspiracy theories that imagine Blute as the victim of
an elaborate political dirty trick.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's speculation all over the city about whether this is a
set-up,'' said one source close to Massport.
</P>
<P>
   Yet other sources pointed to Churchill's attendance at the
Cellucci fund-raiser with David McCool, a close friend of Blute and
Tennant, as a sign that she was not likely to be part of a plot to
embarrass the former Massport chief.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
