</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
AIMS-TEST _ Arizona's new high school graduation test may be in
jeopardy because of a lawsuit begun seven years ago by parents who
say the state does not do enough to educate Spanish-speaking
children. The case winding its way through U.S. District Court in
Tucson contends that the AIMS is discriminatory against
limited-English students as a graduation requirement. If a judge
agrees, the test could be declared unconstitutional. By PATRICIA
BIGGS. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL;
